        <para id="id4465931">To portray the rattle of the skeletonâ€™s bones, the composer used the <emphasis effect="bold">xylophone.</emphasis></para>
        <para id="id1167430934939">What does the xylophone look like?</para>
        <para id="id1167432971513">The xylophone is a percussion instrument and is struck with hammers.</para>
        <para id="id8312038">It consists of a series of oblong wooden blocks of different sizes.</para>
        <para id="id8740063">
          <emphasis effect="bold">Now paste in (or draw) a picture of a xylophone</emphasis>
          <emphasis effect="bold">.</emphasis>
        </para>
        <para id="id5883007">How is sound produced on the xylophone?</para>
        <para id="id8310817">The wooden blocks are struck with hammers to produce sound.</para>
        <para id="id5714938">Different hammers are used for different timbres, e.g. wood, rubber and felt.</para>
        <para id="id4306612">The shorter and thicker the wooden blocks, the higher the sound; the longer and thinner the blocks, the lower the sound.</para>
        <para id="id2844396"><emphasis effect="bold">T</emphasis>HE<emphasis effect="bold"> P</emphasis>ITCH: The notes of the xylophone are relatively high.</para>
